Chrony Configuration #  Chrony is an implementation of NTP, it allows for the pi&rsquo;s to synchronize their time even if internet is not connected to one of them. It acts as a daemon in the background. So when setup it should never need to be reconfigured or edited with afterwards.
Client Configuration (student Pi) #  Go in the Pi terminal type &lsquo;sudo apt-get install vim-y&rsquo; to install vim, (a unix text editor) make sure you are connecting to the correct router on the rasberry pi, then to find your ip type &lsquo;ip a | grep inet&rsquo;, and copy the third line with &lsquo;inet&rsquo;, (may differ: should read something such as &lsquo;10.10.20.153/24&rsquo;, only copy the fist section, in this case that would be &lsquo;10.10.20.153&rsquo; type &lsquo;vim /etc/chrony/chrony.conf&rsquo;
Below the initial comment, (above all other code) write in a new line: &lsquo;server &lt;copied_ip&gt; iburst prefer&rsquo; where &lt;copied_ip&gt; is the item you have just copied then finally save the document by pressing Ctrl + C, typing &lsquo;:x&rsquo; and pressing Enter. (you should have now returned to the original terminal window) then type &lsquo;systemctl restart chrony&rsquo; to check if the server is working, type: &lsquo;chronyc sources&rsquo;
